Ogun Governor Dapo Abiodun has eased lockdown of the state. He declared the weekdays – Mondays to Fridays- free for movement and business activities between 6am and 8pm. Saturdays and Sundays, according to him, would be observed as total lockdown. The new eased lockdown, Abiodun added, takes effect from Monday, June 1st. The Governor made these known on Thursday evening at the Oke – Mosan Governor’s Office while addressing newsmen.     